section.def:
mid-length
                (船長度中點) means the mid-point of the subdivision
            length of the ship;

tr.td:
maximum positive
                                    righting lever (in metres) within the range as given below but
                                    not more than 0.1 m;

is the height of the horizontal subdivision above the baseline
                                   (in metres) which is assumed to limit the vertical extent of
                                   damage;
